ie.cit.group3.entity

Class Users

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.cit.group3.entity.Users

  • @Entity
public class Users
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    john murphy This class is used as the form backing bean to gather and display user related data. Actual passwords and account status are not recorded by this class - the 'User' class is used for these (encrypted password and enabled attributes). I tried to combine the attributes in this class with the attributes from 'User' class, but it would not work for me. This is why there areseparate Users' object/entity.
